summary: This is an email from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) regarding a letter to the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME). The OCME requested that the letter and a prior letter be withheld from disclosure, and the office plans to send the letter by the close of business.

events.title: Email Regarding OCME Letter
events.description: An email is sent from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York discussing a letter to the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner and the OCME's request to withhold it and a prior letter from disclosure.

keyFacts: The document is an email dated September 9, 2019, concerning correspondence with the Office of the Chief Medical Examiner (OCME).
The OCME requested that a letter and a prior letter be withheld from disclosure.
The U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York planned to send the letter by the close of business on that date.
